libvdpau
------------------------------------------
VDPAU is the Video Decode and Presentation API for UNIX. It provides an
interface to video decode acceleration and presentation hardware present in
modern GPUs.

 * Hardware decoding of MPEG-1, MPEG-2, MPEG-4 part 2, H.264, VC-1, and DivX 4
   and 5 bitstreams on supported hardware, with a bitstream (VLD) level API.
 * Video post-processing including advanced deinterlacing algorithms, inverse
   telecine, noise reduction, configurable color space conversion, and procamp
   adjustments.
 * Sub-picture, on-screen display, and UI element compositing.
 * Direct rendering timestamp-based presentation of final video frames, with
   detailed frame delivery reports.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.25-1
  libvdpau-devel-0.7-1bl1
  libvdpau1-0.7-1bl1
  libX11-devel-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.23.51-1
  cygport-0.13.0-1
  gcc-core-4.7.3-1
  gcc-g++-4.7.3-1
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/VDPAU

Canonical download:
  http://people.freedesktop.org/~aplattner/vdpau/libvdpau-0.7.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libvdpau-0.7-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
         unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libvdpau-0.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libvdpau-0.7-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libvdpau-0.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libvdpau1-0.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libvdpau-devel-0.7-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libvdpau)
  /etc/vdpau_wrapper.cfg
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libvdpau.README
  /usr/share/doc/libvdpau/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libvdpau/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libvdpau/COPYING

(libvdpau1)
  /usr/bin/cygvdpau-1.dll
  /usr/lib/vdpau/cygvdpau_trace.dll
  /usr/lib/vdpau/libvdpau_trace.la

(libvdpau-devel)
  /usr/include/vdpau/vdpau.h
  /usr/include/vdpau/vdpau_x11.h
  /usr/lib/libvdpau.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libvdpau.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/vdpau.pc

